title: The Tale
author: MSF_Sunset
pages:
#- There lies a tale of this warrior.

My tongue cannot speak it.

Do not let his story go untold.

Seek out his sisters in Versailles. Their riders will tell of 
#- magnificent tales and wonderful adventures

Take care of this steed. He is wise beyond reckoning.

Do not doubt him, he will not doubt you.


#- Seek the tale of Siegmeyer.

-Sunset.

"I won't scatter your sorry to the heartless sea."

"I will always be with you."
#- 